who writes on livejournal these days?
wait, lets try this again..
who has time to write on livejournal these days?

my life has been flashing by me, i hope im using my time well. time management is a blissful thing honestly. lets see.. major things.. i went to arizona for spring break with the tennis team, it was good times. we climbed a mountain of cactii(i still have a thorn in my foot) and we visited the grand canyon. i brought back a piece of cactus for bryan.
our 1 fat year anniversary is on the 22 of this month. crazy huh. i love this time of year bc it reminds me of when we were getting to know eachother. its fun memories.

i have started to realize why i love it here, and why i hate it here.
love first?
its such a mixing bowl. ill admit when i first got here it was overwhelming, but now i am just blooming with curiousity to try new things. thai food, watching indian movies.. i even wore a viel yesterday like the muslim/islamic(oh i don't want to be wrong about this) women. it was hot. walking through my campus center we have questions all over the place like history of the islams and just a constant ethnic diversity. then theres me, totally white. lol. i swear im trying to learn spanish, i get the basics.
hate.hate.hate.
there is such a stereotype for women up here. we are supposed to get our nails and hair done every other week. every week if there is a social event. crazy. plus we are supposed to be all about shoes and fashion. we aren't supposed to like many sports or be able play them[football]. we are supposed to be appealing all the time.. even if it is freezing cold outside. its all about materialism, not many sentimental things found up here.
 
girls are girls and guys are guys. here at njit it might not be so bad, but in the real nj/ny life this is the dealio. it aggravates me that i say somethign and guys challenge me like, oh i thought girls aren't supposed to be into that. get real we aren't some kinda disease.. we are who we are. i am who i am and i don't like having someone expect me to be girly, and i don't want someone to expect me to be guyish. im grace, nice to meet you. my sisters understand this, but some of my guy friends just don't get it. others i realllyyyy don't give a shit.

im going home for a day(finally) for easter, i get to see my baby niece and relax(sorta).
enough for now... and the next few months.

it was a mistake, it wasn't my fault.. but it was.
why wont he understand
how did this happen
its like an awful nightmare, i can't believe this
its over.. its over its over. 
i just can't believe it.
its funny, how i always looked from here outwards... and now all i wanna do is go back, from outward in.

wow. so my dad put the laptop on his credit card, and i pay him monthly. i move into my apartment on the 27, but im leaving on the 23 bc i can't stand my parents. ha ha ha.
well i mean, i just keep getting into fights with them. today i went to ikea and i got a futon mattress for my awesome futon my sister made me. and a desk! its so awesome, i mean it has a place for everything. those ikea people must think a lot, i want to work for them. it has a place built in, like a little wall you can write on with eraser marker, and its magnetic, and it has a place for cd's and dvd's and books and odds and ends, on i fell in love at first sight.

yesterday was my last day at work. it went alright. im going there tonight to treat my parents to dinner for their birthdays. yeah they are getting pretty old, its a good thing all their kids are grown up and a grandkid has popped out already.
my weird boyfriend bought a new house by his new college, in his new town. (no need to say im jealous i think you could pick that up yourself) hes all about that right now... yeah..
i have been so lucky, since i only worked three days this week i got to hang out with people i should have hung out with a long time ago. like katie fitzerwack, and katie rielly and becky and julie, and christa! awesome times. i went ot kings dominion and then katie and i went shopping for back to school, she saved me a whole ten dollars! what about that 'ish? don't you wish she could do that for you?!?!
im in a really good mood if you havne't noticed.

i opened up a bank of america account the other day. i feel so old, i dind't even have my dad go with me, i set it up myself. i get checks with this account, and i get to sign my name and everything, and the card will have my little picture on the bottom of it. wahoo.

dude, i haven't packed, at all. my room looks so messy, but i have to have it straight before i leave otherwise that will be something that my mom will get on my everytime i talk to her, ... even though i will have no power over it cuz im at college...

i got a new phone, its sooo pretty. maybe this one will last, i don't think ill throw this one into the air, or throw it against the wall, or drop it into a cup of water(haha danielle), or let donut fungus grow in the charger part. i made a promise to it that i woudln't let anything happen to it, like nemo's dad did in the beg. of finding nemo. yeah, im weird. but its so ... confusing, it has alot of colors in everything and its so complex... maybe summer and the blonde has gotten to me and i have sunken to a new low of stupidity.

last minute hang out time ends on the 22,tomorow, bc i think i have to dedicate all of monday packing.
call my cell bc again...i have very few numbers.

SO, i haven't updated in awhile. I've been working a lot, not that it shows in my paycheck. I went to NJ the other week, i swear i thought it would get easier throughout the summer, but everytime i see that boy it gets harder to walk away. I went to OC just this past day and it was cool.

I've come to the conclusion that im not the person i was when i left charles county. I still haven't made the decision if its a good thing or not. I don't have any problem with who i am now, except for the fact that i don't mesh as well with some people that i did before. I haven't even seen katie fitz since i have been back. Weird or no? I mean its my fault. But my point is even though everyone says it, "oh college isn't gonna get between us" it does. (this doesn't have to do with any particular person, in general). I just don't even know who i am when i am down here, i am living two seperate lives, i think everyone who goes far away to college does. Its different people, different environment, rules, priorities... two different worlds. When i come down here i don't fit it where i used to, and its been driving me up the wall this summer. I don't feel right around people bc i don't know how to feel.

I thought identity crisis' were when i came to school with mix matched clothing or avril-like clothes. I've never heard of it when you are going into your second year of college. But thats whats goign on with me right now. I feel like the only people that understand me, well the only person that understands me is bryan. Everythingi s just so weird for me right now. But goign to the beach, at night i went out there by myself and watched the waves and thought, until the cop told me i wasnt' allowed on the beach then. But in those few minutes i was i realized that i just want to have fun, i need to its summer after all. I can have fun by myself or with other people. I like both, so i am just gonna have fun, lose every ounce of drama that surrounds me and fill it with happy people, if you wanna do that too im your girl. I just really wanna have lunch with katie.

I wanna hang out with other people too, but like i said before i don't have your freakin number. Yeah thats you katie rielly and julie and becky. ha. So yeha hit me up, and hopefulyl i won't be losing my cell phone for a long time now.

wow it feels good to let some thoughts out.

i feel like im so outta the loop from everyones life. ive been really busy with work, and some other bad 'ish in my life. its too much and i just want to keep working to pass the time til i go to NJ again on tuesday. so i guess i should say i lost all the numbers in my cell phone, so if you wanna hang out you gotta call me, bc i obviously can't call you, but i wanna hang out with everyone, so ... tell me about things lol.
congrats to the class of '05 i saw most of you WAHOO!
but yeah... not the best of days im tellin you that.

well i haven't had time to realyl use this thing. 
but i have a few funny stories that need to be logged.
this past weekend was awesome, very very awesome. I played softball and went fishing, played badminton, asshole (AND THROUGHOUT THE WHOLE WEEKEND I WAS ONLY ASSHOLE ONCE, I WAS EVEN PRESIDENT AND VICE MANY OF TIMES...) football catch, and oh it was just awesome. 
**i also saw the movie CRASH, i seriously, seriously, recommend it to EVERYONE. its one of the best movies i've ever seen. seriously.
I got to spend five days with Bryan, now really, thats just awesome in itself.

Now for the real funny story... its the weirdest experience i have been in so far...
(sorry if this grosses anyone out, it wasn't my intention, but the point is hilarious)
ok so i have this big "surgery" thing to go to, so i get there and they take me to this room and they are like ok we need to check your body pulse and blood pressure and whatev. and so they do, then they put me in this rooma nd they said to change into scrubs, so i do, full scrubs, the ucky apron and the hair wrap and the footie things, and then they are like ok we are gonna go to the surgery room now, and im like cool and i start walkin and they are like no... sit in this chair, so i do, and they said lay back, and it lays out, and then roll me across the center into the surgery room like i can't walk or something, then they are like, are you ok to get on this bed? and im like yeah... and so i do, then they cover me with tons of blankets, and then they make me lay my arms out on either side one to constantly monitor my blood pressure and the other my pulse, and i saw my heartbeat on a machine and heard the beat and everything like i was on ER or something, then they put this sensor thing on my thigh, and a tourniquet around my ankle to cut off my circulatoin and then they make my foot an ugly color and then they put all those sheets on top so only the part of my foot shows, and then they do the injection of numbness and things start rollin, and its over in like ... 3 minutes
and all of that shit just for a fuckin wart, and they wouldn't let me walk again, and they bandaged it up to my ankle,like an inch thick,so i had to get the ucky blue shoe to walk in and i was laughing the WHOLE time bc it was hilarious the measures they went through for this
PLUS they gave me a prescription for tylenol codeine if the pain got to me
is that weird or what?!
so the first chance i had i ditched the shoe, got it rewrapped so i could where my work shoes, and it hasn't bothered me at all....

yeah so i have two jobs now. i really like the Gustavo's one, i haven't realyl technically started the other one, but tomorow i will... i am learning spanish from the mexican chef's, everyone there is realyl awesome and warm hearted, its a great place to work at i think. 

as you can see im in a really good mood. thats rare for the past couple of days so yeah. yay.

well since all my college friends are doing their im home entry. i wanna re-do mine, bc it was whiny and yeah..
I didn't want to be home, lol. But i think now that i got back into the grove it will be ok. Its killing me being away from Bryan, i didn't realize it would be this hard. I didn't realize how much charles county could change. Its true, its not the same home i grew up in, people keep moving down here, and things keep popping outta the ground(things like buildings... not crops..)
I really didn't see much people from college until like.. friday, so seeing christa and julie and katie and becky, ... and beating them all at bowling [;)] was really fun for me. THEN i saw bobby and went to stephen mattingly's on saturday and saw matty and john and erica and carl and joey peel and *sigh* well just a lot of people and that was good times. SO i am doing good now. And i saw jessica on sunday, but we missed the chocolate covered strawberries. 
I am currently employed at Gustavo's. Come, eat, tip well, because i get 2% of that, lol. I am a bus girl/ soon to be food runner, so i can be a waitress one of these days.
I should be packing... but uhh what a procrastinator i am. My house is still a crazy mess, and everytime i try to clean something my mom yells at me. There was this random kid at my house, and i was watching her, and she punched me right above the boob, it hurt a lot. She was only three years old too, i wanted to punch her right back, but ever since i broke my phone i am learning to restrain myself...
yup, can't' wait til tomorow, back to dirty jersey for some good ol' campin. Im gonna stink...

im home.

I was so excited about coming home. Its my first whole day home and i am stuck in some bad situations. They all lead back to money problems. I am really hoping i get this job, my interview is tomorow and i am passive nervous. I am kinda mad that i missed the Finch concert, but it also meant i got home sooner, and i guess its true, i didn't really want to be driving three hours back that late. I am going camping with Bryan and some of his frat dudes on memorial day weekend. Thats all i have ot look forward to.
    My house doesn't feel like home. There are so many vehicles in the driveway, and people here non-stop bc my mom's dream of fixing up the house has finally come true. My grandparents moved out of their house to an assisted living space, since my grampa's been in pretty bad shape. All the stuff my parents didn't want thrown out is now in my house, not like we didn't have enough extra shit in here already. Some rooms are half painted needing to be finished and everything is just crazy. I wanted to cry bc i felt so ... not belonging here. I was so afraid about the day i would come home and it woudln't feel like "home", and that day was yesterday. I told my mom today that i will paint the rooms if she gives me the color, i want to help out as much as i can, bc i can see my dad is getting burnt out. I also don't want bryan to come down here thinking i live in this wreck, lol. Im growing up. Christan said that i have matured, just that im different, she said it wasn't in a bad way but you know how ppl don't want to put you down.
    I need this job, and another one. My dad took out a 14000 loan for this years tuition, and next year isn't going to be any better, well it will bc im not living in the dorms, but i think i lost my scholarship bc of my grades... I need to stay with tennis now, and request for more money. And i need to get a weekend job up there too. My dad said i am going to be paying for my rent, thats 300 a month. I am going to be piss broke. Plus i need to pay for my ocean city trip somehow. My truck is indeed broke again, i dind't even get to drive it. I have to prolly find money to fix that too, since our mechanic is the one here non-stop helping to close in our carport. I need money just to get by for now too, my parents never gave me money, i always had a job, and now i am broke trying to figure out how i am going to get by until my first paycheck. Looks like i have to go to my sister again. I hate being so dependent. I am going to be so busy, its a good thing though, bc it will get my mind off missing bryan.

whos up for some good news, bad news? because i have plenty of both and i don't know what to do with all this extra time on my hands... studying just doesn't seem fit. lol.

GOOD NEWS:
The womens tennis team is the first in NJIT history to reach NCAA championships, and i get to go.
I got 85 dollars back on my tax refund, and i didn't pay in the first place.
Studio is over, and i get to sleep aallllll day if i'd like.
Classes are over, just waiting for my finals.
I get to go home in a week and ... 4 days.
I might possibly hit a Finch concert on the way down.

I HAVE AN INTERVIEW FOR A SUMMER JOB AT A CIVIL ENGINEERING/ARCHITECTURE FIRM!! and its right in La Plata.
I am very content where i am with relationships.

BAD NEWS:
I'm sick.
I have been sick for almost two weeks now.
I am getting everyone else sick.
The antibiotics don't work, they make me feel worse.
I sleep waay to often because of my sickness.
I haven't started studying for those long awaited finals.
I am going to miss everyone up here in New Jersey soooooo much this summer.

Well, my good outnumber my bad. 9-7. Everyone can post their good news, bad news, because sometimes it makes you happier! Like the other time...

haha but really...





to think i am going to be in maryland for three months... four hours away, goddamnit why is it i get stuck in long distance things?

i kinda want to go home, not because up here is bad, being up here is awesome right about now. Barely any classes left, and lots of good time spent on my hands. I just still want to go home, i think christan needs me, and of course i always need her. I want to see my sister, and my family. My sister from north caroline will be home next week but thats during my finals so i can't see my neice. She is so cute, i see the pictures and i just want to drive the ten hours to see her. New Jersey is so crowded and city-like, but just being home in the less populated area is soo relaxing.
I miss Christan, late nights spent just talking til 4am, falling alseep to eachothers voices(that soudns real weird i know). I can't hate her, lol, i wish i could that butt hasn't called me,  but uhh its a love hate thing i guess. Lol. I think im seeing finch on the 15th which makes everythng more happy, as long as they are good atleast. oh well... im tired, im sick! I've been sick for like a week now, and it won't go away. arg.

Wow. this past week has been so busy. Obviously, lol, i haven't even had enough time to put thought into updating my journal. I am so happy to say that studio and tennis is over. I wish my final review went a little better. Its not that i got bashed or anything, i didn't get to present half of my work because we ran out of time. I was really really mad about that.

Lets see.. i went rock climbing!!! This past week was spring week at our school, so they had fun activities going on throughout the week, like rock climbing, foam parties, and spring formal. I got up that wall so quick! I beat a lot of guys, GO GIRL POWER! haha, jk. I went to the spring formal because one of my friends won MS NJIT (go nikki ;)) so she got free tickets. It was ok.

I just realized that the formals New Jersey people had, even at their proms are totally different than ours. They get sit down dinners, and we have some meatballs on the side, lol. It happens i guess...

I have had the weirdest dreams lately, like ones that are so close to reality, like reliving what i did that day but in a different way, i can't seperate dreams from reality anymore. But last night i had a really bad dream, you could call it a nightmare actually. It was with strictly NJIT people, mostly the guys at NJIT. I was at some party and there were some really creepy guys that i have never seen before. They kept hitting on me, not the kind of "hitting on" that is like i want you, but the kind that is like im going to get you, whether you like it or not. They wouldn't let me be, or leave, i was stuck there. I kept looking for my guy friends but the only ones i could find i coudln't get near. I finally found one of my good friends, and he tried to get me out, but they killed him. It was really bad, i know this sounds so weird guys, but it seriously freaked me out. I woke up to an unsettling phone call, and couldn't get back to sleep. I am so freaked out by it.

So really... i don't have much to do here besides my math and CIS classes... and those end soon too, but my finals aren't til may 9 and 10. Then im still stuck here till the 14, but then ill be home for THREE WHOLE MONTHS!!! And i can go see my niece, and drive my truck, and relax. HAHA, no, find a fucking job lol. I need to work hardcore this summer.

But otherwise, im so happy.  ;)

AND FOR ALL OF YOU WHO ARE MAD BECAUSE I DIDN'T CALL. WELL I AM SORRY! I REALLY DIDN'T HAVE TIME YESTERDAY UNTIL I WAS INFRONT OF A COMPUTER WAITING.

i had a dream that my truck got fixed and prettied up and colored white with new rims and tires and everything... and then i just told my dad about it, and he said that it DID get fixed!!! its not all prettied up, but i don't give a shit,,... CHIMPENDALE IS BAACK!!!! i am so fuckin happy!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
I CAN'T WAIT FOR SUMMER!!!

ive been soo busy, actually im so busy right now i shouldn't be wasting my time on this, but sometimes writing helps me.

I had my mid review for my final prohect on monday, it went pretty well actually, i was in a good place, and then like... thursday it took a turn for the worst. Everyone around me has issues they are dealing with, so do I. I hate that because how are you supposed to help your friends when you can't even get your own life straight?

Lately everything has been tennis, tennis tennis. We had a match on wednesday, friday, saturday(today) and we have one tomorow. Im so aching. I guess the only good thing about it is im really improving, people always told me im inconsistent, and now i am very consistent.

 I don't know when im going to get this archie work done, im trying now but im so tired i can't think. After my tennis match last night i did sneak in a girls night, because i needed it. I went with Amy and Hala to see Miss Congeniality 2 and it was pretty good. Then we went to some odd diner and had depressingly bad food and finally slept at Hala's house.

 Im working backwards. Its been a beautiful week. Maybe thats why im so unfocused on my work. I have alot due on monday, grr. I cna't believe my final is in less than two weeks.

 

 But i would like to declare one thing. I've met a guy, and everything has been quite--- quite well.  Im in the "giddy" stage and i think thats the only thing keepin me going now. // :) \\

oh how i wish i enjoyed this weekend, i have been busy. Busier than if it was a regular weekday... It was irritating, missed the best party of the year... and had tennis which was ok. Im still debating on if i want to do it next semester. Im sitting here in studio with one shoe on because the other got a major knot in it by ONO. THANKS. I also only have a 10 oclock class tomroow so i can work on it then too. So its not that bad,... just FUCKING IRRITATING! I've had enough.

So because of her stupidity, it escalated to this. So my tennis match was in southern pennsylvania on saturday, so my sister and mom drove up and got me. I got to be home for easter!! I tried to see as many people as i could on saturday, but it sucked because i got back at like... 830, so my time was limited. I saw jessica and jessica, and that was really nice to catch up with them. I saw Katieeee and her bro, and we watched kill bill, i forgot how scary it can be. And i saw danielle, christan, and bobby. I can see they are shutting me out already. the one night i come home and christan spends it with bobby instead of me... whatev! lol. Its so weird, when i come home, i love spending time with my friends, but when im just driving around in my car i feel so... outta place, or its realyl weird, like something is missing. Im so scared of the day that i go home, and its not home anymore. Thats like my greatest fear because i love it soo o o o O much. But then i woke up butt ass early on sunday and went to church. The church that i used to go to when i was a wee little pickle. It got renovated since then, Leena Vansickle was there so i said hi, and guess what? She went there when she was little too, she remembered me. It just goes to show that i really don't remember much from growing up, my memory is SHOT. Then i went to my grammas for dinner. It was a suprise for well everyone because they didn't know i was coming down. My gramma from the other side and my uncle and aunt from the other side came, and so did my aunt and uncle from this side. It was so cool seeing everyone, especially since i haven't seen my uncle and aunt much when i was growin up because they were in nevada. It was really an awesome dinner, awesome food and dessert. Then i played pool with my dad and uncle and sis' and my uncle kicked my ass. Everytime i was about to get a shot in he would block it. He said "grace its a dog eat dog world out there, and you're wearing milkbone underwear." hehehehe I also beat my sister in GIN which by the way never happens. But she won the 2 outta 3. Then i hopped on my greyhound and went to newark. It was PACKED, and the traffic was really built up, but i was only like... half an hour late, lol. Got back, went to studio... and then slept. 

There is the play by play if anyone wanted to read. Sorry i flooded your friends page.

so... my aunts mom died today. and i just realized, wow, the things that can happen. She was such an awesome old lady. I like spending time with them, but everyone has such busy lives, i wish there was some kinda way we all dind't get so wrapped up in other things to realize hey your missing out and need to be with your family.

since valentines day is approaching, and i am in a bad mood, i thought i would declare my thoughts on valentines day now....

love is a crazy thing. some say its a devotion to another person, a feeling. you can feel loved, be in love, make love, give love... all those things. but to actually know what love is is unnatainable. I being me, haven't been in love, and i don' t know when i will be. I "love" my friends and sisters, to the point that i know. I "love" my family. But to be able to put those feelings into words is the problem for me, and most of the world.

They say you only fall in love once, ha. i don't think so. I thought i was once, nah, definetly not. I think i will be soon... but who knows when people don't call.

This was going to be the first time that i thought i wouldn't care what happened on vday, i would get a call, i knew i would, and i would be perfectly happy. To be honest im giving a lot up now, in hopes that it will all pay off for summer. I don't think i will get a call on Vday, and I can't really be mad, hes a busy person.

But here i am goign crazy over something thats still a week away. I was going to be fine, and i will be, its just all this Vday love is getting in the air and catching the sorrow love bug.

Don't worry, i brought my anti vday shirt, so i will be rockin that on monday. HA
